.TH "pci_raw_set_power_state" 9 "pci_raw_set_power_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_raw_set_power_state \- Use PCI PM registers to set the power state of given PCI device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_raw_set_power_state
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "pci_power_t state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device to handle.
.IP "state" 12
PCI power state (D0, D1, D2, D3hot) to put the device into.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
RETURN VALUE:
-EINVAL if the requested state is invalid.
-EIO if device does not support PCI PM or its PM capabilities register has a
wrong version, or device doesn't support the requested state.
0 if device already is in the requested state.
0 if device's power state has been successfully changed.
